---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Digital Liberation Front - Build the Alternative">

  <Hero slot="hero" headline="Digital<br/>Liberation<br/>Front">
    <p class="hero-label" slot="label">Built in San Francisco</p>
    <div class="intro-content">
      <p class="intro-tagline">Building a people &amp; worker-owned digital future</p>
      <p class="intro-body">We were born in San Francisco&mdash;the same city that birthed the monopolies now gripping our world. We watched them rise from garages and dorm rooms into empires.</p>
      <p class="intro-emphasis">This is where they started. This is where the alternative starts too.</p>
    </div>
  </Hero>

  <section class="manifesto">
    <div class="manifesto-inner">
      <p class="manifesto-lead">We're millennial-led, and we remember.</p>

      <div class="remember-block">
        <p>We remember buying books at stores, not from Bezos.</p>
        <p>We remember social connection without Zuckerberg's algorithms.</p>
        <p>We remember when "tech" meant possibility, not extraction.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="manifesto-body">We watched these platforms take over. We saw local economies collapse. We saw democracy weaponized. We saw billionaires capture the digital infrastructure of our lives.</p>

      <p class="manifesto-turn">And we know it doesn't have to be this way. Because we remember when it wasn't.</p>

      <div class="manifesto-declaration">
        <p>We're not going back to the hierarchical capitalism that came before.</p>
        <p>We're not accepting the monopolistic extraction of now.</p>
        <p class="declaration-bold">We're building democratic ownership of modern technology. Worker-owned platforms. User-governed networks. Cooperative marketplaces.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="manifesto-body">We're not starting from scratch. Platform cooperatives already exist. Worker-owned businesses have been organizing for decades. Labor unions have fought for economic democracy for generations. We're joining that movement&mdash;amplifying existing work, organizing new builders, creating the infrastructure we need.</p>

      <p class="manifesto-body">We partner with labor unions, cooperative networks, and people-powered movements. This future requires all of us: tech workers who build the platforms, service workers who run them, users who depend on them, organizers who mobilize communities.</p>

      <p class="manifesto-body">Gen Z, Gen X, Boomers&mdash;we need you. This is a multi-generational project. We're building the future together.</p>

      <p class="manifesto-closer">They won't be the future. We will be.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <nav class="section-nav" id="section-nav" aria-label="Page sections">
    <div class="section-nav-inner">
      <a href="#vision" class="section-nav-link">Vision</a>
      <a href="#2026" class="section-nav-link">2026</a>
      <a href="#social" class="section-nav-link">Social</a>
      <a href="#commerce" class="section-nav-link">Commerce</a>
      <a href="#get-involved" class="section-nav-link">Get Involved</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <!-- The Vision -->
  <section class="content-section" id="vision">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="accent-bar" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <h2>The Vision</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">By 2045, every major digital service people depend on has a co-op alternative—owned by users, governed democratically, and impossible to sell to billionaires.</p>
      <p class="generation-call">Millennials and Gen Z, we're looking at you. The time is now to build the future we want. <span class="generation-aside">(Boomers and Gen X, and all others of course welcome to join.)</span></p>

      <div class="domain-grid">
        <div class="domain-card">
          <span class="domain-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M16 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M22 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/></svg></span>
          <h3>Social & Communication</h3>
          <p>Social networks, messaging, and photo sharing owned by the people who use them.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="domain-card">
          <span class="domain-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 2 3 6v14a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h14a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V6l-3-4z"/><line x1="3" x2="21" y1="6" y2="6"/><path d="M16 10a4 4 0 0 1-8 0"/></svg></span>
          <h3>Commerce & Local Economy</h3>
          <p>Marketplace co-ops owned by local merchants. Money stays in your community.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="domain-card">
          <span class="domain-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polygon points="23 7 16 12 23 17 23 7"/><rect width="15" height="14" x="1" y="5" rx="2" ry="2"/></svg></span>
          <h3>Media & Streaming</h3>
          <p>Film, music, and news platforms that pay creators fairly and aren't beholden to advertisers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="domain-card">
          <span class="domain-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 16V8a2 2 0 0 0-1-1.73l-7-4a2 2 0 0 0-2 0l-7 4A2 2 0 0 0 3 8v8a2 2 0 0 0 1 1.73l7 4a2 2 0 0 0 2 0l7-4A2 2 0 0 0 21 16z"/><polyline points="3.27 6.96 12 12.01 20.73 6.96"/><line x1="12" x2="12" y1="22.08" y2="12"/></svg></span>
          <h3>Organizing & Collaboration</h3>
          <p>Tools for movements, unions, and communities—built to empower, not surveil.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="vision-note">Four domains. Twenty years. We start with two.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Starting in 2026 -->
  <section class="navy-section" id="2026">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="accent-bar" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <h2>Starting in 2026</h2>
      <p class="section-lead light">We're not trying to build everything at once. We're starting with two domains where the need is most urgent and the path is most clear.</p>

      <div class="start-cards">
        <div class="start-card">
          <span class="start-card-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M16 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H6a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M22 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/></svg></span>
          <h3>Social & Communication</h3>
          <p>Replace Instagram, Facebook, and X with platforms we own and govern.</p>
          <a href="#social" class="card-link">See the plan &darr;</a>
        </div>
        <div class="start-card">
          <span class="start-card-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 2 3 6v14a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h14a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V6l-3-4z"/><line x1="3" x2="21" y1="6" y2="6"/><path d="M16 10a4 4 0 0 1-8 0"/></svg></span>
          <h3>Commerce & Local Economy</h3>
          <p>Replace Amazon with city-based marketplace co-ops owned by local merchants.</p>
          <a href="#commerce" class="card-link">See the plan &darr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="why-these">
        <h3>Why these two?</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Immediate need:</strong> Social platforms are how billions connect. Amazon dominates commerce. These are the biggest leverage points.</li>
          <li><strong>Proven models:</strong> Co-op grocery stores, credit unions, and mutual aid networks already work. We're applying the model to digital platforms.</li>
          <li><strong>Community exists:</strong> Millions of people are already looking for alternatives. The demand is there.</li>
          <li><strong>Builds momentum:</strong> Success in these two domains proves the model and funds expansion into media and organizing tools.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <p class="future-note">Media & Streaming and Organizing & Collaboration come next (2028+). First, we prove the model works.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Social & Communication -->
  <section class="content-section" id="social">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="accent-bar" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <h2>Social & Communication</h2>

      <div class="subsection">
        <h3>The Problem</h3>
        <p>Every major social platform is owned by a billionaire who has bent the knee to authoritarianism. Meta gutted fact-checking. X became a right-wing megaphone. TikTok's fate is decided by politicians, not users. Our social lives are controlled by people who don't share our values—and we have zero say in how these platforms work.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="subsection">
        <h3>What We're Building</h3>
        <p>User-owned social platforms structured as cooperative corporations. Every user is a member-owner. Major decisions—moderation policy, algorithm design, data practices—are voted on democratically. The platform can never be sold to a billionaire because the members own it.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="subsection">
        <h3>What Already Exists</h3>
        <div class="proof-cards">
          <div class="proof-card"><h4>Bluesky</h4><p>Decentralized, open protocol. Already millions of users. Not a co-op (yet), but its open protocol means no single entity controls it.</p></div>
          <div class="proof-card"><h4>Mastodon</h4><p>Federated social network. Community-run instances. Proves decentralized social media works at scale.</p></div>
          <div class="proof-card"><h4>Signal</h4><p>Nonprofit encrypted messaging. 40M+ users. Proves you don't need ads or data harvesting to build great communication tools.</p></div>
          <div class="proof-card"><h4>Pixelfed</h4><p>Decentralized Instagram alternative. No algorithm, no ads, no Meta. Photo sharing the way it should be.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="subsection">
        <h3>What Still Needs Building</h3>
        <ul class="needs-list">
          <li>A co-op social platform that's as polished and intuitive as Instagram—optimized for real connection, not engagement metrics</li>
          <li>Cooperative governance structures that scale to millions of users</li>
          <li>Sustainable revenue models that don't depend on advertising or selling user data</li>
          <li>Migration tools that make switching from billionaire platforms painless</li>
          <li>Interoperability between co-op platforms so users aren't locked in</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="subsection">
        <h3>Skills Needed</h3>
        <div class="skills-grid">
          <span class="skill-tag">Mobile developers (React Native, Swift, Kotlin)</span>
          <span class="skill-tag">Backend engineers (distributed systems)</span>
          <span class="skill-tag">UX/UI designers</span>
          <span class="skill-tag">Co-op governance experts</span>
          <span class="skill-tag">Community organizers</span>
          <span class="skill-tag">Content moderation specialists</span>
          <span class="skill-tag">Legal (co-op incorporation)</span>
          <span class="skill-tag">Product managers</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="subsection project-highlight">
        <h3>Current Project: Kith & Kin</h3>
        <p>A social app that optimizes for closeness, not clout. Share photos, gratitude, and moments with the people who matter most—not an algorithm. Currently transitioning to a user-owned co-op structure based in San Francisco.</p>
        <div class="project-status">
          <span class="status-badge">In Development</span>
          <span class="status-detail">SF-based &middot; Becoming a co-op in 2026</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Commerce & Local Economy -->
  <section class="navy-section" id="commerce">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="accent-bar" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <h2>Commerce & Local Economy</h2>

      <div class="subsection">
        <h3>The Problem</h3>
        <p>Amazon has hollowed out local economies. Independent bookstores, hardware shops, and artisans can't compete with a company that runs at a loss to crush competitors. Jeff Bezos spiked the Washington Post's endorsement of Harris, pays workers poverty wages, and spends millions busting unions. Every Prime subscription funds this.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="subsection">
        <h3>What We're Building</h3>
        <p>City-based marketplace co-ops owned by local merchants. Imagine Amazon's convenience—search, browse, buy online, get delivery—but the merchants own the platform. Revenue stays in your city. No billionaire middleman taking a 40% cut.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="subsection">
        <h3>What Already Exists</h3>
        <div class="proof-cards">
          <div class="proof-card"><h4>Bookshop.org</h4><p>Online bookstore that supports independent bookshops. Has distributed over $30M to indie stores. Proves the model works for books.</p></div>
          <div class="proof-card"><h4>Stocksy</h4><p>Artist-owned stock photography co-op. Members earn 50-75% of sales (vs. industry standard of 15-45%). Co-op model, profitable.</p></div>
          <div class="proof-card"><h4>REI</h4><p>Consumer co-op with 23M+ members. $3.7B in revenue. Proves co-ops can compete at massive scale in retail.</p></div>
          <div class="proof-card"><h4>Local food co-ops</h4><p>Thousands of food co-ops across the US. Community-owned, locally sourced, worker-friendly. The OG model we're building on.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="subsection">
        <h3>What Still Needs Building</h3>
        <ul class="needs-list light">
          <li>A marketplace platform that's as easy to use as Amazon—search, buy, track, return</li>
          <li>Logistics and delivery infrastructure that works for local merchants</li>
          <li>Merchant onboarding tools that make joining the co-op simple</li>
          <li>Payment processing that minimizes fees for small businesses</li>
          <li>City-by-city launch playbooks so this can replicate everywhere</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="subsection">
        <h3>Skills Needed</h3>
        <div class="skills-grid">
          <span class="skill-tag light">E-commerce developers</span>
          <span class="skill-tag light">Logistics & operations</span>
          <span class="skill-tag light">UX/UI designers</span>
          <span class="skill-tag light">Local business organizers</span>
          <span class="skill-tag light">Payment systems engineers</span>
          <span class="skill-tag light">Marketing & growth</span>
          <span class="skill-tag light">Legal (co-op incorporation)</span>
          <span class="skill-tag light">Data & search engineers</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="subsection project-highlight project-highlight-dark">
        <h3>Current Project: SF Marketplace Co-op</h3>
        <p>Starting in San Francisco with books and home goods. Local bookstores, artisans, and makers own the platform together. One city first, then the playbook goes open source for every city.</p>
        <div class="project-status">
          <span class="status-badge">Planning Phase</span>
          <span class="status-detail light">SF-based &middot; Launching 2026</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How to Get Involved -->
  <section class="content-section" id="get-involved">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="accent-bar" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <h2>How to Get Involved</h2>

      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-number" aria-hidden="true">1</span>
          <div class="step-content"><h3>Pick a Domain</h3><p>Social & Communication or Commerce & Local Economy. Choose what excites you—or where your skills fit best.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-number" aria-hidden="true">2</span>
          <div class="step-content"><h3>Join the Community</h3><p>Connect with builders, designers, organizers, and researchers already working on this. Monthly calls, async collaboration, and working groups.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-number" aria-hidden="true">3</span>
          <div class="step-content"><h3>Contribute What You Can</h3><p>Write code. Design interfaces. Research co-op models. Organize merchants in your city. Test prototypes. Every contribution matters.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-number" aria-hidden="true">4</span>
          <div class="step-content"><h3>Launch in Your City</h3><p>The playbooks and platforms we build are open source. Take what we learn in SF and launch a marketplace co-op, a social platform chapter, or an organizing hub where you live.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="principles">
        <h3>Our Principles</h3>
        <ul class="principles-list">
          <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#x2713;</span> Democratic ownership—one member, one vote</li>
          <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#x2713;</span> No venture capital—we don't build things to sell them</li>
          <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#x2713;</span> Open source—the code belongs to everyone</li>
          <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#x2713;</span> Privacy by design—your data is yours</li>
          <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#x2713;</span> Fair compensation—workers and creators get paid fairly</li>
          <li><span class="check" aria-hidden="true">&#x2713;</span> Local first—money stays in communities</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA + Form -->
  <section class="final-cta-section" id="join-build">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Join the Build</h2>
      <p class="final-cta-lead">This isn't a petition. It's not a protest. It's a construction project. We're building the digital infrastructure we wish existed—and we need your help.</p>

      <div class="cta-grid">
        <div class="form-wrapper">
          <h3>Get Involved</h3>
          <form method="POST" action="https://formspree.io/f/xdagvzav" class="build-form" id="build-form">
            <input type="text" name="_gotcha" style="display:none" tabindex="-1" autocomplete="off" />
            <input type="hidden" name="_subject" value="Digital Liberation Front - New Builder Signup" />

            <label for="build-name">Name</label>
            <input type="text" id="build-name" name="name" placeholder="Your name" required />

            <label for="build-email">Email</label>
            <input type="email" id="build-email" name="email" placeholder="your@email.com" required />

            <label for="build-city">City</label>
            <input type="text" id="build-city" name="city" placeholder="Where are you based?" />

            <fieldset class="form-fieldset">
              <legend>What domain interests you?</legend>
              <div class="checkbox-group">
                <label class="checkbox-label"><input type="checkbox" name="domain" value="Social" /> Social & Communication</label>
                <label class="checkbox-label"><input type="checkbox" name="domain" value="Commerce" /> Commerce & Local Economy</label>
                <label class="checkbox-label"><input type="checkbox" name="domain" value="Media" /> Media & Streaming</label>
                <label class="checkbox-label"><input type="checkbox" name="domain" value="Organizing" /> Organizing & Collaboration</label>
                <label class="checkbox-label"><input type="checkbox" name="domain" value="Other" /> Other / Not sure yet</label>
              </div>
            </fieldset>

            <fieldset class="form-fieldset">
              <legend>What skills can you contribute?</legend>
              <div class="checkbox-group">
                <label class="checkbox-label"><input type="checkbox" name="skills" value="Developer" /> Developer</label>
                <label class="checkbox-label"><input type="checkbox" name="skills" value="Designer" /> Designer</label>
                <label class="checkbox-label"><input type="checkbox" name="skills" value="Organizer" /> Organizer</label>
                <label class="checkbox-label"><input type="checkbox" name="skills" value="Researcher" /> Researcher</label>
                <label class="checkbox-label"><input type="checkbox" name="skills" value="Legal" /> Legal</label>
                <label class="checkbox-label"><input type="checkbox" name="skills" value="Other" /> Other</label>
              </div>
            </fieldset>

            <label for="build-message">Anything else?</label>
            <textarea id="build-message" name="message" placeholder="Tell us about yourself, what you'd like to work on, or any questions..." rows="4"></textarea>

            <button type="submit" class="form-submit">Count me in</button>
          </form>
          <p class="form-success" id="form-success" hidden>Thanks! We'll be in touch soon.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="community-links">
          <h3>Join the Community</h3>
          <div class="community-card">
            <h4>Monthly Builder Calls</h4>
            <p>First Tuesday of every month<br/>8pm ET / 5pm PT</p>
          </div>
          <div class="community-card">
            <h4>Discord</h4>
            <p>Day-to-day collaboration, working groups, and async discussion.</p>
            <span class="coming-soon-badge">Coming soon</span>
          </div>
          <div class="community-card">
            <h4>Bluesky</h4>
            <p>Follow for updates and join the conversation.</p>
            <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/defundbillionaire.bsky.social" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="community-link">@defundbillionaire &rarr;</a>
          </div>
          <a href="https://defundbillionaires.org" class="back-link">&larr; Defund Billionaires</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</BaseLayout>

